It appears that esm@3.0.32 introduced a bug on how `instanceof` is handled with NodeJS builtins.

```
const EventEmitter = require('events')
const Stream = require('stream').Stream

const myObject = new Stream()
console.log(myObject instanceof EventEmitter)
/* true in vanilla Node.js, false with esm 3.0.32 */
```

This works as expected with esm@3.0.31.

